"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088345","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-18","<p>NHS England does not hold information on the number of National Health Service trusts in England that have outsourced cancer treatment services.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-03-18T16:25:54.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088345/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088345/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088345/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-13","Cancer: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent estimate his Department has made of the number of NHS trusts in England that have outsourced cancer treatment services, in part or in whole, to private sector providers.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","231900"
