"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088470","Home Office","false","2019-03-21","<p>The Home Office does not centrally hold the information requested.</p><p>The timely and effective management of investigations is an operational matter for the police. The Home Office continues to work with partners across the criminal justice system, including the National Police Chiefs’ Council to ensure that all investigations are conducted effectively and in a timely fashion.</p><p><br>From April 2017, the Home Office requested information on a voluntary basis from police forces on the number of individuals released on pre-charge bail following arrest, broken down by bail length.</p><p>This data collection has been published (as an Annex) within the ‘Police powers and procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletin, based on data received from 17 forces for the 2017/18 financial period. These figures give an indicative picture only and should be treated with caution – they have been designated as ‘Experimental Statistics’, to acknowledge further development will take place in the future. They can be accessed here:</p><p><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2018</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","231945 ; 231947","2019-03-21T15:24:36.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088470/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088470/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088470/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-13","Criminal Investigation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of those released under investigation by the police in the last 12 months for which figures are available had no case brought against them.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","231944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088471","Home Office","false","2019-03-21","<p>The Home Office does not centrally hold the information requested.</p><p>The timely and effective management of investigations is an operational matter for the police. The Home Office continues to work with partners across the criminal justice system, including the National Police Chiefs’ Council to ensure that all investigations are conducted effectively and in a timely fashion.</p><p><br>From April 2017, the Home Office requested information on a voluntary basis from police forces on the number of individuals released on pre-charge bail following arrest, broken down by bail length.</p><p>This data collection has been published (as an Annex) within the ‘Police powers and procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletin, based on data received from 17 forces for the 2017/18 financial period. These figures give an indicative picture only and should be treated with caution – they have been designated as ‘Experimental Statistics’, to acknowledge further development will take place in the future. They can be accessed here:</p><p><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2018</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","231944 ; 231947","2019-03-21T15:24:36.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088471/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088471/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088471/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-13","Criminal Investigation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people were released under investigation by the police in the most recent 12-month period for which figures are available by each police authority.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","231945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088472","Home Office","false","2019-03-21","<p>The monitoring of compliance with pre-charge bail conditions is an operational matter for the police, taking into account the circumstances surrounding individual cases.</p><p>The Home Office will continue to work with partners across the criminal justice system on matters related to pre-charge bail. The National Police Chiefs’ Council are leading work to ensure the proportionate and effective imposition and management of pre-charge bail and released under investigation.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-03-21T15:25:46.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088472/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088472/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088472/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-13","Bail: Monitoring","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what procedures are in place to monitor compliance with bail conditions.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","231946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088473","Home Office","false","2019-03-21","<p>The Home Office does not centrally hold the information requested.</p><p>The timely and effective management of investigations is an operational matter for the police. The Home Office continues to work with partners across the criminal justice system, including the National Police Chiefs’ Council to ensure that all investigations are conducted effectively and in a timely fashion.</p><p><br>From April 2017, the Home Office requested information on a voluntary basis from police forces on the number of individuals released on pre-charge bail following arrest, broken down by bail length.</p><p>This data collection has been published (as an Annex) within the ‘Police powers and procedures, England and Wales’ statistical bulletin, based on data received from 17 forces for the 2017/18 financial period. These figures give an indicative picture only and should be treated with caution – they have been designated as ‘Experimental Statistics’, to acknowledge further development will take place in the future. They can be accessed here:</p><p><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2018</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","231944 ; 231945","2019-03-21T15:24:36.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088473/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088473/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088473/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-13","Criminal Investigation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average waiting time is for a person who has been released under investigation to be contacted by an investigating officer.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","231947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088474","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-03-21","<p>In 2010/11 Government, through the Office of Low Emission Vehicles, spent £7.3m and in 2018/19 is forecast to spend approximately £200m. This is part of Government’s programme of investment, alongside other measures set out in the Road to Zero strategy, to put the UK at the forefront of the transition to zero emission vehicles.</p><p> </p><p>In 2018, the UK was the second largest market for ultra low emission vehicles in the EU accounting for nearly 20% of registrations, and 1 in 5 electric cars sold in Europe last year was made in the UK.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2019-03-21T13:33:39.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088474/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088474/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088474/answer","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088474/answer/previousversion/108505","Biography information for Richard Harrington","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-03-13","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the total value has been of government spending on subsidies for the manufacture and purchase of low emission and electric vehicles in (a) 2010-11 and (b) 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","232031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088475","Home Office","false","2019-03-19","<p>Whenever a person suspected of committing an offence is questioned under caution about their involvement in an offence, the interview must always be recorded whether or not they have legal representation. These rules are set out in Codes C, E and F of the Police and Criminal Evidence Act 1984.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-03-19T17:32:43.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088475/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088475/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088475/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-13","Police Interrogation: Recordings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether interviews are recorded when a person is interviewed by the police without legal representation.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","231948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088476","Home Office","false","2019-03-18","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on police recorded motoring offences and how they have been resolved by the police. These data are broken down by offences which led to a Fixed Penalty Notice and/or financial penalty; attend a driver retraining course; or face court action which may lead to prosecution. These statistics do not provide the outcome of those summoned to court and therefore do not provide the number of individuals prosecuted for motoring offences.</p><p>Data on prosecutions for motoring offences are held by the Ministry of Justice and are published in their quarterly ‘Criminal Justice Statistics’ bulletin. The Ministry of Justice has published data on the number of prosecutions for motoring offences, by Police Force Area, up to December 2017, and can be found here:<br><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733991/motoring-tool-2017-update.xlsx%20" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733991/motoring-tool-2017-update.xlsx </a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2019-03-18T16:48:41.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088476/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088476/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088476/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-13","Road Traffic Offences: Prosecutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many prosecutions for motoring offences were pursued by the police (a) overall and (b) in each police force area in each year since 2009.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","231892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088477","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-18","<p>The information requested is not centrally held.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-03-18T16:26:39.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088477/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088477/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088477/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-13","Diabetes: Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people have been diagnosed with gestational diabetes in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","231937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088478","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-21","<p>Neither the Department nor NHS England hold an attendance register for the two webinars offered following publication of the engagement report.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-03-21T16:23:46.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088478/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088478/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088478/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-13","Tomography: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many (a) patients and (b) members of the public took part in the two webinars related to the procurement process of PET-CT scanning services.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","232104"
