"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088544","Cabinet Office","false","2019-03-18","<p>Details of high-value exit payments in the Civil Service, including number, type, compensation levels, and cost of exits, are published each year in Departmental Annual Reports and Accounts.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-03-18T15:11:30.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088544/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088544/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088544/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-03-13","Civil Servants: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants received exit payments in excess of £95,000 in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Sir Christopher Chope","231883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088545","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-18","<p>The Department does not collect this data. Local authorities are independent employers and, as such, Government has a limited role in local government workforce matters. Data from the Government Actuaries Department, which looked at 36,232 redundancies covering 2013-2016 (the most recent data available) suggested that 7.7 per cent would have had exit payments in excess of £95,000, including any pensions strain cost that may have been payable to their pension fund. HM Treasury is leading on reforms to public sector pay and will be consulting on how the cap will work in practice shortly. MHCLG will be responsible for implementing those arrangements for local government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2019-03-18T17:21:55.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088545/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088545/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1088545/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-13","Local Government: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many local government employees have received exit payments in excess of £95,000 since 1 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Sir Christopher Chope","231884"
